race.comment: JUST GLAMOUROUS (3) firmed from 3.2 to 2.6 but was weak late and missed the placings in a small field last start over 1400m at this circuit. A heavy track may have contributed to that poor effort. Very fit after two runs back and with a bit of weight relief against the boys today she can bounce back. AUTOMNE TREE (8) hit the line with purpose to get up for third when resuming over 1400m at Hawkesbury last time out. Improved sharply at the second run last prep. Back in good order so despite the rise in class he is a definite contender. IVAN'S HERO (12) went back in trip for the second start in a row but did a good job to finish third at Warwick Farm recently. Nicely placed today and makes plenty of appeal down on the limit. MORTAL HALO (11) started favourite and dominated first-up in a 1400m Scone maiden. Tested at stakes level three times in six starts so the stable has an opinion. Right in the mix. CLIMB THE LADDER (6) has been a shade disappointing but a step up in trip may help.
